article.headline: George Mason 89, Delaware 59
article.story: FAIRFAX, Va. (AP) -- Folarin Campbell scored 21 points to lead George Mason to an 89-59 victory over Delaware on Wednesday. George Mason (13-9, 7-5 Colonial Athletic Association), which led 44-27 at the half, opened the second half with a 21-11 run that included five 3-pointers to put away Delaware. Dre Smith hit a career-high four 3-pointers and scored 12 points. Will Thomas added 14 points, while John Vaughan contributed 12 for the Patriots, who shot 63.3 percent (31 of 49). Delaware (4-19, 2-10) was led by Herb Courtney's 16 points. Sam McMahon (14 points) and Darrell Johnson (11) also scored double figures for the Blue Hens, who have dropped 10 of their last 12. The Patriots, who scored a season-high 89 points, opened their first double-digit lead, 22-12, on a 3-pointer by Smith at 10:38 of the first half. George Mason's largest lead was 82-48 and came on a free throw by Campbell with 5:23 remaining in the game. In addition to hitting 9 of 15 3-point attempts, the Patriots outscored the Blue Hens 42-22 in the paint. The Patriots have won four straight games in the series, including seven of eight meetings in Fairfax.
